title: The Medieval Islamic Civilization - Col.18 (Art, Architecture 5)
description:
The Medieval Islamic Civilization - Collection 18 (Art, Architecture 5):

We have 10 titles here:

-  Bennison & Gascoigne (Eds.) - Cities in the Pre-Modern Islamic World; the Urban Impact of Religion, State and Society (2007)

-  Goodwin - Islamic Spain; Architectural Guides for Travelers (1990)

-  Horioka et al - Oriental and Islamic Art in the Isabella Stewart Gardner Museum (1975)

-  Islamic Art and Geometric Design; Activities for Learning, The Metropolitan Museum of Art (2004)

-  Kadoi & Szanto (Eds.) - The Shaping of Persian Art; Collections and Interpretations of the Art of Islamic Iran and Central Asia (2013)

-  Kahera, Abdulmalik and Anz - Design Criteria for Mosques and Islamic Centers; Art, Architecture and Worship (2009)

-  Leacroft & Leacroft - The Buildings of Early Islam (1976)

-  Mamluk Art; the Splendour and Magic of the Sultans, 2e (2010)

-  Robinson & Pinet (Eds.) - Courting The Alhambra; Cross-Disciplinary Approaches to the Hall of Justice Ceilings (2008)

-  Treasures of the Aga Khan Museum - Arts of the Book & Calligraphy (2010)
